cs.RO, cs.HC, cs.LG, cs.SY, cs.CV 

Reasoning: 
- cs.RO (Robotics): The paper focuses on designing and implementing experiments to collect and process human data for improving walking and push recovery controllers for humanoid robots. 
- cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction): The paper explores control laws applied by human beings for push recovery, which can potentially improve the performance of humanoid robots. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper uses data-driven methods for model fitting and analysis of human motion data. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper proposes a proportional-derivative (PD) control model to describe the underlying control law used by people for push recovery. 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition): Although not the main focus, the paper mentions using motion capture technology to collect human motion data.
